```ts
let response = NextResponse.next({...})
// ...
const supabase = createServerClient(..., {
  cookies: {
    get: ...,
    set(name, value, options) {
      request.cookies.set(...)
      response = NextResponse.next({...})
      response.cookies.set(...)
    },
    remove(name, options) {
      request.cookies.set(...)
      response = NextResponse.next({...})
      response.cookies.set(...)
    },
  },
})
```

Since the `intlMiddleware(request)` returns a `NextResponse`, the reassignment in the cookie callbacks also works the same way — they'll overwrite with a fresh `NextResponse.next()`. This should be fine.

